notes:
this semi-circle lace shawl/scarf wraps around the upper body and the bobbles can be used instead of a shawl-pin, very nifty. you can also wear it as a scarf. i also made two shawls and put it together with buttons to form a poncho.  if you use a dk (3 weight) yarn, make sure to use a 4.5mm crochet hook and you will need a bit of extra yarn (max 650 meters). i've made it in fingering and dk. it is suitable for summer and winter, depending on the yarn you choose. this pattern is beginner friendly.

stitches used: chains, single crochet, double crochet.
this pattern has a hyperlink to a video tutorial, should you prefer the tutorial above the written pattern.

materials used:
•	recommended: red heart it’s a wrap rainbow, 150g, 600m. 2 weight yarn. 45% cotton/55% acrylic blend. 
•	size 4mm crochet hook
•	wool needle to work in ends
•	scissors
•	4x stitch markers (optional)

abbreviations:
ch - chain;    
sc - single crochet;  
dc - double crochet;  
sts - stitches;  
st - stitch;  
yo - yarn over hook; 
slst - slip stitch;  
sk - skip.

